§§ Properties ⦉
<statement type='proposition' text='Adjoint is Linear'>
  ‖ Suppose $T ∈ ℒ(V, W)$. ⦉

  ‖ The adjoint of $T$ is linear. ⦉
</statement>
<statement type='proposition' text='Adjoint properties'>
  ‖ Suppose $V$ and $W$ are finite dimensional inner product
    spaces over a field $𝗙$, which is $𝗥$ or $𝗖$. ⦉

  ‖ Suppose $S, T ∈ ℒ(V, W)$. ⦉

  ‖ Then
    𝍫 ⦊
      ‣ $(S + T)^* = S^* + T^*$ ⦉

      ‣ $(λT)^* = \Cconj{λ}T^*$ for all $λ ∈ 𝗙$ ⦉

      ‣ $ (T^*)^* = T$ ⦉

      ‣ $ I^* = I$ ⦉
    ⦉⦉
</statement>
<statement type='proposition'>
  ‖ Suppose $V$, $W$, $U$ are finite dimensional inner product
    spaces over $𝗥$ or $𝗖$. ⦉

  ‖ For all $T ∈ ℒ(V, W)$ and $S ∈ ℒ(W, U)$,
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ (ST)^* = T^*S^* ⦉
    ⦉⦉
</statement>
